item.dc:creator: @Wintercanon Wintercanon
item.description:
@Wintercanon wrote:

Community Member is not a post-count title, it’s a custom group awarded to valued community members. You’re probably thinking of Senior Member, in which case you could probably reach by spamming before you are completely disliked by the community or perhaps banned.

Edit: The CPU is usually dubbed as just the processor, is usually measured spec-wise in GHz and by how many cores it has. If you want to upgrade and keep current, go buy an Intel i7 quad-core.
